Spec: Init Command
Purpose:
  Initialize SpecDD in the current directory or a target directory.

Structure:
  init.ts: Init command implementation.
  init.test.ts: Init command tests.

Owns:
  init.ts
  init.test.ts

References:
  ../container.sdd
  ../services/distribution-installer/service.sdd

Must:
  Expose a factory for the init command.
  Receive a Container-compatible dependency object.
  Set a concise command description for help output.
  Accept an optional target path argument.
  Describe the optional target path argument in help output.
  Resolve a missing target path to the current working directory.
  Resolve a relative target path against the current working directory.
  Pass an absolute target path through as the target directory.
  Accept an optional release version option.
  Describe the release version option in help output.
  Include the project copyright notice in help output.
  Include SpecDD framework and CLI project help links in help output.
  Default the release version to latest.
  Call DistributionInstaller.init with the resolved target directory and release version.
  Support construction by the Container.

Must not:
  Construct application services.
  Download, verify, or apply distributions directly.
  Implement the CLI entrypoint.

Depends on:
  commander
  Container
  DistributionInstaller
  Node.js path handling

Exposes:
  createInitCommand(container)

Accepts:
  optional target path
  optional release version

Returns:
  commander Command
